      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the \"it depends\" thing, but that feels like a bit of an easy answer for a paper. if you had to look at the actual historical track record, doesn't the research mostly point to nationalism being a precursor to major conflicts and instability? like, is it even possible for it to be \"good\" in the modern world without eventually turning into something harmful?",
